      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Detail of outcome</h2>

      <div class="consultation-outcome-detail">
        
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>This document summarises the responses to the review consultation and explains next steps. It will be of interest to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>the owners and operators of crematoria in England (referred to as “providers”)</li>
  <li>local burial authorities with statutory responsibilities to provide and maintain burial grounds or cemeteries including the provision and maintenance of crematoria</li>
  <li>faith and other community groups in England</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

      </div>



      <section class="original-consultation">
        <header>
          <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  " id="original-consultation-title">Original consultation</h2>

        </header>


    <section class="app-c-banner app-c-banner--grid" aria-label="Notice">
      <h2 class="app-c-banner__title">Summary</h2>
  <p class="app-c-banner__desc">
          Review to establish whether crematoria provision and facilities are suitable to meet the demand and cultural requirements of all communities.

  </p>

    <p class="app-c-banner__desc">        This consultation ran from<br></br><span class="consultation-date"><time datetime="2016-03-16T00:00:00.000+00:00">16 March 2016</time> to
        <time datetime="2016-05-26T00:00:00.000+01:00">11:59pm on 25 May 2016</time></span>
</p>
</section>


      </section>


    <div class="consultation-description">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Consultation description</h2>

      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>We are carrying out a review of crematoria provision and facilities to establish whether they are suitable to meet the demand and cultural requirements of all communities.</p>

<p>The review is being carried out in response to concerns about the capacity of crematoria, in particular to accommodate Hindu and Sikh cremations at which traditionally larger numbers of mourners wish to attend. In addition, there have been concerns that crematoria do not always pay sufficient regard to the cultural sensitivities of different faiths.</p>

<p>We want to use this review to establish whether the concerns that have been raised are widespread. We are therefore seeking the views of all faith communities and users of crematoria, whether they are of a faith or none.</p>

<p>We are also seeking views from the providers of crematoria, including local authorities and the private sector, as well as the Local Government Association and industry representative bodies. The government will publish a summary of responses in due course and consider whether any policy changes are needed in light of the evidence received.</p>
</div>
</div>


